.. django app antey enti?
an app = a small module inside ur project that does one specific feature.
simple rule:
one feature = one app

If your website is ‚Äúmovie booking‚Äù, you might create apps like:

Feature	               App name
Users              login/signup	users
Movies             list	movies
Booking            tickets	booking
Payment             gateway	payments
Reviews & ratings	    reviews
each app ni separete ga create chestamu..

app lo maanki models.py , views.py , admin.py apps.py
models.py :- database tables for this app
views.py :- logic for this app
admin.py :- admin site lo display
apps.py :- config for django

Why do we create apps? (Very important)
1Ô∏è‚É£ To separate features cleanly
If your whole website code is in one project ‚Üí total mess.
Apps divide work like departments in a company.
2Ô∏è‚É£ To reuse code
You can take one app and reuse it in another project.
Ex: auth app
Django itself gives reusable apps.
3Ô∏è‚É£ To manage big websites easily
Facebook, YouTube, Instagram ‚Äî anni hundreds of apps tho build chesaru.
Each team works on one app.
4Ô∏è‚É£ To follow MVC/MVT structure properly
Models, Views, Templates ‚Äî app lo group ga untayi.
‚≠ê Simple way to remember:
üëâ Project = Entire website
üëâ App = One feature of the website

üß° Simple Analogy

Oka college (project)
Andulo:
Students Dept (app)
Teachers Dept (app)
Exams Dept (app)
Fees Dept (app)
Each department = separate app.
College = main project.


